{"TopicId":196182,"ForumId":24,"TopicTitle":"Must New Versions of KSP be purchased at full price?","CreatedByName":"StephenMZ","CreatedById":206677,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-08-08T08:38:42Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"StephenMZ","CreatedById":206677,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-08-08T08:38:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI bought KSP earlier this summer and downloaded 1.9.1 directly through the free\u00A0 version.\u00A0 Now I see 10.1 is listed on Curse?\u00A0 Can I get such upgrades without paying $40.00 for another full game download?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"James Kerman","CreatedById":160462,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-08-08T08:52:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWelcome to the forum \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/206677-stephenmz/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022206677\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/206677-stephenmz/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@StephenMZ\u003C/a\u003E, the upgrade to 1.10 is free however the method of upgrade differs depending\u00A0on where you purchased the game.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Deddly","CreatedById":62955,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-08-08T08:53:34Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHi \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/206677-stephenmz/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022206677\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/206677-stephenmz/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@StephenMZ\u003C/a\u003E, where did you get the game from? Steam should update automatically, but if you got it from the KSP Store, it\u0027s a little different, as James said.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"StephenMZ","CreatedById":206677,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-08-08T09:37:56Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI bought KSP directly from the developers through the free version, earlier this year.I did not use Steam, though I considered it.\u00A0 I did not want to subscribe to a service, just buy and play..\u00A0 What should I do to update?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThank you for your help.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-08-08T09:44:03Z\u0022 title=\u002208/08/2020 09:44  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00223 yr\u0022\u003EAugust 8, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by StephenMZ\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003Eadditions to question.\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"James Kerman","CreatedById":160462,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-08-08T09:42:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223834120\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022196182\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221596879476\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022206677\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022StephenMZ\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 minutes ago, StephenMZ said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI bought KSP directly from the developers through the free version, earlier this year.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn that case you can go to \u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.kerbalspaceprogram.com/store/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ethe KSP store\u003C/a\u003E, login to your account and download the latest version.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"StephenMZ","CreatedById":206677,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-08-08T09:47:16Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOK, great.\u00A0 I\u0027ve tried to log n earlier today, but claims my email or password is incorrect.\u00A0 I will try again.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"James Kerman","CreatedById":160462,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-08-08T11:28:23Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223834124\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022196182\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221596880036\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022206677\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022StephenMZ\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, StephenMZ said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI will try again.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you continue to experience problems, please\u00A0\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#353c41;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003Eemail \u003Ca href=\u0022/cdn-cgi/l/email-protection\u0022 class=\u0022__cf_email__\u0022 data-cfemail=\u00229eedebeeeef1eceadef5fbecfcfff2edeefffdfbeeecf1f9ecfff3b0fdf1f3\u0022\u003E[email\u0026#160;protected]\u003C/a\u003E for assista\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#353c41;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003En\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#353c41;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003Ec\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#353c41;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003Ee.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"StephenMZ","CreatedById":206677,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-08-08T21:36:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nRoger, wilco, James!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Singhnaut","CreatedById":207340,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-09-24T22:35:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou can just go to your account on kerbalspaceprogram.com and then click download again. DO NOT MOVE THE FILE!!!!! I can not stress this enough, it will only make things harder\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Gargamel","CreatedById":64714,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-09-25T03:36:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223859143\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022196182\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221600986929\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022207340\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Singhnaut\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 hours ago, Singhnaut said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDO NOT MOVE THE FILE!!!!! I can not stress this enough, it will only make things harder\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNo it doesn\u0027t.\u00A0 It\u0027s very common and an easy to do.\u00A0 Moving the downloadable zip, and the installed game, to allow for multiple custom installs is a very common practice.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}